# CVE-2026-33671 — picomatch vendored inside next/dist/compiled/picomatch
#
# This copy of picomatch is bundled directly into the Next.js distribution and
# cannot be upgraded independently via pnpm. We have already upgraded Next.js
# to the latest available release (16.2.3). This finding will be resolved
# automatically when Next.js ships an updated compiled bundle.
CVE-2026-33671

# The following 10 CVEs are in transitive dependencies of devDependency toolchain
# packages (ESLint, Prisma CLI, Turbo) that land in the image because the full
# node_modules is copied to make `prisma migrate deploy` available at runtime.
# None of these packages are invoked by the web server's request path; they are
# only present to support the Helm pre-upgrade migration Job.
#
# @hono/node-server (transitive dep of @eslint/plugin-kit)
CVE-2026-29087
#
# defu (transitive dep of Nuxt/build tooling pulled in by Turbo or Prisma CLI)
CVE-2026-35209
#
# effect (used internally by Prisma 7 CLI)
CVE-2026-32887
#
# flatted (transitive dep of ESLint flat config)
CVE-2026-32141
CVE-2026-33228
#
# hono (transitive dep of @eslint/plugin-kit via @hono/node-server)
CVE-2026-29045
#
# lodash (transitive dep of build tooling; lodash 4.18.0 is not yet published)
CVE-2026-4800
#
# minimatch (transitive dep of glob/eslint; affects vendored copies at 3.1.2 and 9.0.5)
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904
